        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-19T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-19T04:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/10–1949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-19T16:00:00+07:00">October 19, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 19—7:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 1213. At private dinner early October, Vice Admiral Kwei Yung-ching stated
                    intention strongly hold Chinmen Tao<note n="17" xml:id="d630fn17">Quemoy
                        Island.</note> off Amoy as means interdicting activity there connection
                    invasion of Taiwan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
